column5: Hi all. Haven't posted a report in a while so I thought I'd share a few pics from my trip a couple of weeks ago from Nipissing. A very relaxing week, got to fish with my buddy Lew one morning and spent some great time on the water. Muskies were cooperating quite well and got a bonus pike fish fry. I'll let the pics do the rest of the talking.... View from the cottage and the boat's parking spot... A nice fat 49 and a half incher.... Another chunky fish...46 incher... Nice to see different sizes being caught..my son's first of the week...  My new wall paper for my phone...my two boys and a healthy 43 incher.... and of course some scenery shots.... and the end of the week pike fish fry... I havent figured out the new (to me at least) formatting but thanks for reading. Jim
Awesome Jim you guys have great family trips glad to see Ben out there actually fishing. Can't wait to see you and Corey this year maybe Ben also?
Good stuff man!  I need a week like that.    Badly...
Good work Jim.
Always good spending time with you guys Jim.  Here's that pic I took of you.
Good job Jim.  Looking forward to getting back up that way is less than 2 weeks
Great report. You always do pretty well up there, Jim. Sounds like a great time for you and the lads. Thanks for sharing.  I agree with Lew as well. Beauty boat!
Enjoyed that little diddy Jim.  You should report more often... or at least anytime ya can.  Good fishing and yes, that ski was a fatty!
Dang that is a good looking boat!
Very nice Jim.  Glad the gals were cooperating for you.
You did well my friend. It was good to see you guys again

Thanks for the replies everyone !  Phil- it was great seeing you and PJ again, wish you guys could have stayed longer.  Believer aka Jason-  I'll let you post that pic and make sure you put a disclaimer on it that it is not me LOL  Thanks Joey, sorry we missed you guys this year.  Drew - appreciate the comment, I will try and get some more reports up again.  Roy- its my favorite lake to fish for sure.  Some good karma in that boat, I think the previous owner may have passed it on to me ; )  Rich- there's a 50 incher up there waiting for ya, I have a feeling.  Ned - Missed you up there as well.  Hope all is well.  Mike - you'll be seeing us for sure and Ben has already said he wants to come down this year.
... and the "other" Warden family vacation picture.
You forgot the disclaimer.
lol, i'll let you guys be the judge if it looks like Jim or not.
HAHAHAHAHA  The sad thing is though that even though that gentleman is a tad more "portly" than me, he does bear a resemblance.
